author: Creg Stephenson | cstephenson@al.com
title: Jeb Bush will 'tailgate' at Alabama-LSU, Georgia-Tennessee, Ole Miss-Mississippi State games
text:
Republican presidential candidate Jeb Bush will tailgate with college Republicans prior to Saturday's Georgia-Tennessee football game in Knoxville, and will also appear at the Alabama-LSU game in Tuscaloosa later this year.
According to Bush's official campaign website , the tailgates are designed to "grow a grassroots network and organize in key states." Participants are invited to "come meet Jeb on the field, learn how you can get involved and maybe even take a few selfies."
Bush made his first tailgating stop prior to the South Carolina-Georgia game in Athens last month. Also on Bush's list of stops is the Alabama-LSU game in Tuscaloosa Nov. 7 and the Ole Miss-Mississippi State Egg Bowl in Starkville on Nov. 28.
SEC alums and students are invited to join the Bush campaign by signing up at his website .
